    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>COREL WARNS OF WEAKER RESULTS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Corel Corp, ailing Canadian software developer, warns of smaller sales and bigger loss for second quarter than it previously predicted (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Corel Corporation, the ailing Canadian software developer, warned of smaller sales and a bigger loss for the second quarter than it had previously predicted. Sales for the quarter, ended May 31, are now expected to be $37 million to $38 million, and the loss is estimated at $22 million to $24 million. Corel recently cut 320 jobs, or 21 percent of its work force.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard (NYT)</p>
      </block>
